comments.body: Elegant Trogon is only known from the NW region of the country, where it occurs at much lower elevation. It is actually the only species I haven't seen in CR. The thickness of the tail barring seems a bit variable, or may vary in photos depending on lighting and angle. That being said, I think the barring is still rather bold in relation to to the fine lines in Elegant. Orange-bellied Trogon is the closest in similarity and range, however I believe this individual is red enough to eliminate that option.
Second picture shows detail of tail feathers which seem to be Elegant Trogon. I could be mistaken.
